#!/bin/bash

cat <<EOF
This is a S2I Swift 3.0 CentOS builder image that can turn Swift code into built applications in docker images. To use it, install S2I: https://github.com/openshift/source-to-image

Sample invocation:

$ s2i build https://github.com/dudash/s2i-swift.git \\
    --context-dir=/3.0/test/test-app/ openshift/swift-30-centos7 swift-test-app

You can then run the resulting image via:
$ docker run swift-test-app
EOF